[[media/TAS-UP1-TouchRGB_Proto01_Touch.jpg|height=400px]]

The OpenKNX TAS-UP1-TouchRGB is a modular switch sensor with up to 16 Touch Keys, 16 RGB LED, 10 binary inputs and a I2C sensor interface.<br><br>
It is part of the [[OpenKNX-UP1]] system and designed for usage in switch boxes inside the wall or behind switches (ger: Unterputzmodul).<br><br>
It can be used as a Touch-Switch with one or up to two Touchpanels with up to 8 switches/LEDs each.<br><br>
The sensor interface is meant to connect an air quality sensor.<br><br>
The 10 binary inputs can be used additionally or without the touch functionality - e.g. for connecting reed contacts for windows or to connect "normal" tactile switches like GIRA 14700<br><br>

